  "title": "System Field Engineer (Radar / EO or IMDS) at Ang Mo Kio/ Site (Tuas), Up to $6,000 (Office hours)",
  "description": "<p><strong>- 2-year contract (renewable & convertible)</strong></p><p><strong>- Up to $6,000</strong></p><p><strong>- Mon – Fri: 8:30am–5:30pm</strong></p><p><strong>- Ang Mo Kio/Site (Tuas)</strong></p><p><br /><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>The <strong>System Field Engineer </strong>will be responsible for installing, maintaining, troubleshooting, and upgrading systems and equipment at client sites. This role requires strong technical knowledge, excellent problem-solving skills, and the ability to work independently in the field. The engineer will collaborate with customers and internal teams to ensure optimal system performance and customer satisfaction.</p><ul><li>Install, configure, and commission assigned systems and equipment at customer sites following standard procedures and safety guidelines.</li><li>Perform routine and preventive maintenance to ensure system reliability and performance.</li><li>Diagnose and troubleshoot hardware and software issues on-site to minimize downtime.</li><li>Provide technical support and training to customers / end-users.</li><li>Document service reports, installation procedures, and maintenance records accurately.</li><li>Adhere to company policies, safety regulations, and quality standards.</li></ul><p><strong>Period:</strong></p><ul><li><p>2-year contract (renewable & convertible) </p></li></ul><p><br /><strong>Salary:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Up to $6,000<br /> </p></li></ul><p><strong>Working hours:</strong></p><ul><li>Mon – Fri: 8:30am–5:30pm </li></ul><p><br /><strong>Location:</strong></p><ul><li>Ang Mo Kio/Site (Tuas) </li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree/Diploma/ITE in Engineering in Electronics or equivalent</li><li>Experience in providing maintenance service</li><li>Able to perform 24/7 stand by and able to work out field on site</li><li><p><p>Must be able to lift heavy loads and work at height</p></p></li><li>Good team player and yet able to work independently.</li><li>Valid Class 3 driving license would be advantageous</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Interested applicants, kindly email your detailed resume (MS Word format is preferred):<br /><a href=\"mailto:zikry@successhrc.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">zikry@successhrc.com.sg</a>   (Registration no: <strong>R2198989</strong>)</p><p>Please ensure that applications sent through email are no bigger than 1Mb.<br />We thank all applicants for your interest but regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates would be notified.<br /></p><p><strong>Success Resource Centre Pte Ltd (EA License Number: 04C3201)</strong><br />160 Robinson Road, #13-07/08/09 SBF Center, Singapore 06891<br />T: 6337 3183 | W: www.successhrc.com.sg </p>",
